body:
Several new features are being delivered through the Windows Store version of WSL2, as part of an insiders preview. Such as, systemd support: https://devblogs.microsoft.com/commandline/systemd-support-is-now-available-in-wsl/

This means there could be two version available; the in-Windows delievered WSL binary or one provided by in-store. This might lead to inconsistencies in the deployment or conflicts when someone enables systemd support for the podman machine distro. We might have to do feature detection and enable this accordingly.

@n1hility WDYT?
